To install:

sudo apt-get install ruby1.8-dev libgpgme11-dev libsqlite3-dev libopenssl-ruby1.8

# on new ubuntu
sudo gem install sqlite3-ruby aws-s3 gpgme

# on old ubuntu
sudo gem install sqlite3-ruby -v 1.2.5
sudo gem install aws-s3 gpgme


Then:
  * create yob user on server
  * clone git repository into /home/yob
  * set up 'yob' database user on mysql:
      GRANT select,reload,super,replication client ON *.* TO yob@localhost IDENTIFIED BY 'somepassword'
  * create ~yob/.my.cnf with mysql username and password
